# .rules — modular natural-language data query engine (Rust, Apache-2.0)

> **Read this first — the one source of truth for how we build here.** `AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, and
> `GEMINI.md` all point at this file. Keep it short: the *plan* is [`ROADMAP.md`](./ROADMAP.md), the *why*
> is [`ARCHITECTURE.md`](./ARCHITECTURE.md), the *how-to* is [`CONTRIBUTING.md`](./CONTRIBUTING.md) — link
> them, don't duplicate them.

## What it is
Ask a question in plain English, get an answer **grounded in real data**. Plug in **any LLM** (the `Model`
trait) and **any data provider** (the `DataProvider` trait); a **canonical schema** in the middle contains
each provider's API drift. **Open-core:** the engine, the adapter SDK, and reference adapters are OSS;
hosted / multi-source / team features are additive, never bolted into the core. (Repo is still named
`agent`; the rename is an early task.)

**Flow:** question → `Model` plans a structured query → `DataProvider` returns canonical data → `Model`
grounds the answer. Every surface (CLI, Python SDK, later API) is a **pure view** — none calls an LLM or a
provider directly.

## Commands
| Task | Command |
|------|---------|
| Build | `cargo build` |
| Ask a question | `cargo run -p agent -- ask "…"` |
| No API keys (mock model + mock provider) | append `--mock` |
| Machine output | append `--json` |
| Test (offline, recorded fixtures) | `cargo test` |
| **Local gate — run before every push** | `cargo xtask ci` (fmt + clippy + build + test + feature powerset + deny) |

Stable Rust, one workspace. Live calls hit HTTP APIs; the **mock** adapters keep every command offline with
no keys.

## Layout
```
crates/core       engine: canonical schema, the Model + DataProvider traits, the NL→query→answer flow
crates/models     LLM adapters: mock now; claude + openai + gemini at launch; local next
crates/providers  data adapters: mock now; polygon + yahoo at launch; kalshi/custom next
crates/cli        terminal surface (lib): ask (+ --json)
crates/app        the binary: subcommand dispatch, wires model + provider → engine
xtask             dev/build orchestration (never shipped)
```

## Invariants — never trade these away
The *why* is in [`ARCHITECTURE.md`](./ARCHITECTURE.md) (Design decisions).
- **Headless engine, pure-view surfaces.** CLI, SDK, and API only render the engine's `Answer`, never call
  an LLM/provider directly, and share **one wire contract** — stable field names + exit codes, additive
  changes only, golden-tested.
- **Two seams — `Model` + `DataProvider`.** A new LLM or source is a **new adapter and nothing else**; the
  core depends on neither a specific model nor a specific provider.
- **CLI and Python SDK at parity.** Every engine capability is reachable from both — never CLI-only or
  SDK-only.
- **Async + streaming.** The traits are `async` (`tokio`); answers **stream** token-by-token to every
  surface.
- **Canonical schema defeats drift.** Providers map their raw API → canonical types; the engine and the LLM
  never see raw. A provider's breaking change stays inside its adapter.
- **Capabilities declared; drift caught in CI.** Each adapter states what it can serve, and has
  **golden/contract tests over recorded fixtures** — a provider/LLM contract change fails CI, not prod.
- **Grounded, not advice.** Answers come from fetched data and cite what they used. A **research** tool, not
  financial advice — never fabricate a number.
- **Keyless by default.** The permanent **mock** model + provider build, test, and demo the whole thing
  with no keys — first-class adapters, not throwaways.
- **12-factor config & logs.** Config is layered **flags > env > file > defaults**; secrets come from env
  only; `tracing` logs go to **stderr** (stdout is for output).

## Conventions
- `cargo fmt` + `cargo clippy` clean. Stable Rust, `std`.
- **No `unwrap`/`expect`/`panic!` outside tests** (workspace `deny`; re-allowed in tests via `clippy.toml`).
  A failed model/provider call is an `Err` value that degrades to a clear message — never a panic.
- **Errors:** `thiserror` in the libs (`core`/`models`/`providers`), `anyhow` only at the `app` boundary.
- `#![forbid(unsafe_code)]` workspace-wide (HTTP + serde only — no FFI).
- **Type the domain:** newtypes + the canonical schema, never bare strings/floats across a trait boundary.
  `#[non_exhaustive]` on public types so the schema and wire contract evolve additively.
- **Secrets from env/config only** — never committed, logged, or put in a fixture.
- Each real adapter lives behind a cargo feature; CI builds the default set, `--no-default-features`, and
  the powerset. **MSRV is pinned** (`rust-version`) and CI-guarded.

## Etiquette
- One logical change per commit, imperative subject. **Never add AI co-author / attribution trailers.**
  **Never commit secrets or fetched/generated data.**
- Work in phases that ladder to `v0.1.0`; close each with a **tag + working demo + green CI**. Record
  hard-to-reverse decisions in [`ARCHITECTURE.md`](./ARCHITECTURE.md).

